                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donor; &#xD;
elements of the punctuation signs;&#xD;
elements of Ethiopic numbers;&#xD;
the word salām.&#xD;
A few lines, divided into several groups alternating with black lines, in the pages opening the commemoration notes for each month: &#xD;
10 lines for the month of Maggābit (fol. 7r); &#xD;
8 lines for the months of Miyāzyā (fol. 36r), Sane (fol. 84r) and Ḥamle (fol. 110r); &#xD;
6 lines for the months of Gǝnbot (fol. 57v), Naḥāse (fol. 148v) and Ṗagʷǝmen (fol. 173v).&#xD;
The first two lines of the first commemoration note of the day, one (sometimes two) line of all other commemoration notes.&#xD;
One line of the concluding formula for the month of Miyāzyā (fol. 57rc, l.1);&#xD;
two lines of the concluding formula for the month of Naḥāse (fol. 173rabc, ls. 12-13).</seg>
